snippet.textDisplay:
Maybe in another life,
Maybe in another life we would not be each other's "what ifs," and you would reciprocate my love. I don't know  what I feel for you is love because I don't wanna still be hopelessly in love with you after everything.
I met you when I was 15 and didn't know any better. You were the first (and only) boy I ever truly liked and it was heartbreaking you never liked me back the same way.  All the mixed signals really messed me up you know? For a second it felt like you could sense the connection as well.

16-year-old me would be devastated that I traveled all the way to your hometown and could not meet you.
I am sad that I never got to experience the gorgeous gorgeous place that is your hometown with you—a daydream I've had since I was 16 and hopelessly in love with you. I think I still love you, Whizz, and I think that's why my postcard never reached you. You love her instead because she stays in the real world, unlike me, and you deserve to live your life with her. Sadly, I think I am nothing more than a bitter afterthought. I keep imagining we would totally be soulmates in an alternate universe where the cards were played right and we ended up in the same place. Maybe in this life my love was not yours to receive. But you have her now and I'm happy for you. I can't be crying over a man who has someone else already but you haven't quite literally left my mind since 2020. You haunt all my thoughts and dreams. I don't know who I'd be if I hadn't met you.

Maybe in another life I can call you mine. I wish you all the best, though, and I hope you are happy with her and all your wishes come true. 
Until then, Kashmir shall haunt all my thoughts.
